$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Ukax hexadecimal ukampiw decimal ukat binario valores ukanakar mayjt’ayañatakix apnaqasispa. Amuyt’añataki, 10011011001010 ukax hexadecimal ukar jaqukipañax 0x4F ukaruw purispa. Ukax sañ muniw 4F ukax 100110110010110 uka binario jakhüw uñacht’ayi.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Matemáticas ukat informáticas ukanx hexadecimal (ukax base 16, jan ukax hex) ukax sistema numeral posicional ukawa, ukax radix, jan ukax base, 16. Ukax tunka suxtan chimpunak apnaqi, jilpachax 0–9 chimpunakax cero ukat llätunk chimpunak uñacht’ayañataki, ukatxa A, B, C, D, E, F (jan ukaxa yaqha tuqitxa a–f) tunka tunka phisqhani chimpunaka uñacht’ayañataki. Sañäni, hexadecimal jakhu 2AF3 ukjaxa, decimal uksanxa, (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , jan ukaxa 10.995 ukjamawa.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Sapa hexadecimal chimpuxa pusi binario chimpunaka (bits) uñacht’ayi (ukaxa &quot;nibble&quot; satarakiwa), ukatxa nayrïri apnaqawixa notación hexadecimal ukaxa jaqiru aski uñacht’ayiwa binario codificados valores ukanaka computación ukhamaraki electrónica digital ukanakana. Amuyt’añataki, byte valores ukax 0 ukat 255 (decimal) ukjakamaw utjaspa ukampis juk’amp sumaw pä hexadecimal dígitos ukham uñacht’ayasispa 00 ukat FF ukjakama. Ukhamaraki hexadecimal ukaxa computadora memoria direcciones ukanaka uñacht’ayañatakixa wali apnaqatarakiwa.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'Hex ukax Hexadecimal ukan abreviaturapawa, ukax base -16 ukan uñakipatawa, ukatx kunjams computadoranakar yatichäwinakax uñacht’ayat uk jan ch’amäñapatakiw apnaqasi. Aka sistema de números de 16 símbolos ukax mä medio binario 8 bits ukar jark’aqañatakiw lurasiwayi, ukhamat datos ukanakax computadoranakaruw jan ch’am tukus codificatäspa. Ukax imprimir ukat qillqt’asispawa pä kunayman hexagonal chimpunakampi sapa hexagonal chimpunakampi mä nibble jan ukax inas 4 bits formato uñacht’ayasa.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Aka sistema de números ukax 16 chimpunak apnaqi, ukax 0-9 jan ukax AF ukjakamaw uñacht ayata. 0–9 ukax llätunk jakhunak uñacht’ayi ukatx AF ukax 10–15 jakhüwimpiw uñacht’ayasi. Yaqha kimsa kasta jakhunakampi chikachasiñatakixa, sistema numeral hexadecimal ukaxa juk ampi suma uñjatawa.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'Uka hexadecimal ukax janiw chiqapäkiti';
